8. Conclusion
This paper constructs a toy model of medium optics within the TDMU framework. A medium atom is modeled as a regular graph with dangling ports; starting from the underlying discrete reconnection rules, a continuous wave equation is derived in the long-wavelength limit. Spectral graph theory is rigorously applied to compute the frequency response function 
